@node Intro "Introduction"
@next Install
@prev Author


@{b}@{u}What is ReplyWizard?@{ub}@{uu}

ReplyWizard is a tool for the @{b}Universal Message System@{ub},  with  this  you
can generate automatically replys.

Following @{b}features@{ub} were supported:

   @{b}*@{ub} Scan the private messages:
   @{b}*@{ub} Scan the private messages: folder
   @{b}*@{ub} Generate replys  if  the  attribute  receipt-request  resp.  audit-
     request is set. ReplyWizard also supports replyaddress after receipt-request
     resp.  audit-request. Supported formats:
       RECEIPT-REQUEST="<NAME>,<ADDRESS>"
       RECEIPT-REQUEST="<ADDRESS>"
       RECEIPT-REQUEST="<NAME1>,<ADDRESS1>;<ADDRESS2>;...;<NAMEn>,<ADDRESSn>"
       RECEIPT-REQUEST "<NAME>,<ADDRESS>"
       RECEIPT-REQUEST "<ADDRESS>"
       RECEIPT-REQUEST "<NAME1>,<ADDRESS1>;<ADDRESS2>;...;<NAMEn>,<ADDRESSn>"
       Or AUDIT-REQUEST instead RECEIPT-REQUEST. One mail for every user will  be
       created so you can mix RFC- and Fidoaddress.
   @{b}*@{ub} Generate replys  if  the  attribute  receipt-request  resp.  audit-
     request isn't set (only messages with the  attribute  receipt  were
     not replyed).
   @{b}*@{ub} ReplyWizard can configure global for all users or  local  to  every
     user.
   @{b}*@{ub} You can use your real- or an imaginationname.
   @{b}*@{ub} Foldername for the replys is configureable.
   @{b}*@{ub} Configureable subject, messagetext, replyname and replyaddress.
   @{b}*@{ub} Known variables from IntuiNews  were  partially  supported  in  the
     subject and the messagetext (%s subject, %d date and time, %n  name
     of the sender).
   @{b}*@{ub} A file can used for the messagetext.
   @{b}*@{ub} Archivbit can be set.
   @{b}*@{ub} Replyed messages keep marked as new.
   @{b}*@{ub} Userstatusbit configureable.
   @{b}*@{ub} Program uses the @{b}Guidelines of a  standardized  login-procedure  in@{ub}
     @{b}UMS-programs@{ub}.

@endnode

@node Install "Installation"
@next Config
@prev Intro


@{b}@{u}Installation@{ub}@{uu}

Copy the file @{b}ReplyWizard@{ub} to the other UMS-bin's.

@endnode

@node Config "Configuration"
@next Start
@prev Install


@{b}@{u}Configuration@{ub}@{uu}

   ReplyWizards's  setup  is  mainly  controlled  by UMS   configuration
variables.

   For the configuration you should use ConfUMS  v1.1a  (UMS v10)  resp.
v1.2 (UMS v11).

@{b}UMS configuration variables:@{ub}

   Applications using UMS have  the  possibility  to  access  their  own
variables  in  the  main UMS configuration file. This file is located in
the same directory as the messagebase. Because ReplyWizard  makes  heavy
use of this feature it does not require an own configuration file.

@{b}@{fg highlight}Attention:@{fg text}@{ub}  Because  AmigaGuide  and  MultiView  react  differently   on
backslashes  you  may see two backslashes. Of course you should use only
one in the UMS configuration.

Configuration variables, @{b}global@{ub} or @{b}local@{ub}:

 @{"ĀReplywizard.MaxMsgSizeĀ" link MaxMsgSize}
     memorysize which used for replys.

 @{"ĀReplywizard.UserStatusBitĀ" link UserStatusBit}
     Used userstatusbit to mark messages as replyed.

 @{"ĀReplyWizard.ReplyFolderĀ" link ReplyFolder}
     Name of the folder for the replyed messages.

 @{" ReplyWizard.ArchivBitĀ" link ArchivBit}
     Should the archivbit set ?

 @{" ReplyWizard.FoldersĀ" link Folders}
     List of folders which were scanned. (Replys were only generated  if
     the attribute receipt-request resp. audit-request is set.)

 @{" ReplyWizard.ForceFolders " link ForceFolders}
     List of folders which were scanned. (Replys were always  generated.
     Exeption: The attribute receipt is set.)

 @{"ĀReplyWizard.WizardName " link WizardName}
     Name of the sender.

 @{"ĀReplyWizard.Name " link Name}
     Name of the user for the field @{b}Reply-To:@{ub}.

 @{"ĀReplyWizard.Address " link Address}
     Address of the User for the field @{b}Reply-To:@{ub}.

 @{"ĀReplyWizard.Subject " link Subject}
     Subject for the reply.

 @{"ĀReplyWizard.Msg " link Msg}
     Text for the reply.

@endnode

@node MaxMsgSize "ReplyWizard.MaxMsgSize"
@toc Config
@next UserStatusBit
@prev Config


@{b}@{u}ReplyWizard.MaxMsgSize@{ub}@{uu}

   You can use this variable to define the memorysize for replys.

@{b}Example:@{ub}

     @{b}@{fg highlight}UMS v10@{fg text}@{ub}

     ReplyWizard.MaxMsgSize = "16384"

     @{b}@{fg highlight}UMS v11@{fg text}@{ub}

     ( ReplyWizard.MaxMsgSize "16384" )

@{b}Default:@{ub}

     "8192"

@{b}Remark:@{ub}

     This variable is optional.

@endnode

@node UserStatusBit "ReplyWizard.UserStatusBit"
@toc Config
@next ReplyFolder
@prev MaxMsgSize


@{b}@{u}ReplyWizard.UserStatusBit@{ub}@{uu}

   You can use  this  variable  to  define  the  userstatusbit  to  mark
messages  as  replyed.  This variable is necessary for the compatibility
with other UMS tools which uses the free userstatusbits, too or  if  UMS
needs  a  free  userstatusbit  in  the  future.  You  can choose between
userstatusbit 0, 1, 2, 3, 13, 14.

@{b}Example:@{ub}

     @{b}@{fg highlight}UMS v10@{fg text}@{ub}

     ReplyWizard.UserStatusBit = "2"

     @{b}@{fg highlight}UMS v11@{fg text}@{ub}

     ( ReplyWizard.UserStatusBit "2" )

@{b}Default:@{ub}

     "0"

@{b}Remark:@{ub}

     This variable is optional.

@endnode

@node ReplyFolder "ReplyWizard.ReplyFolder"
@toc Config
@next ArchivBit
@prev UserStatusBit


@{b}@{u}ReplyWizard.ReplyFolder@{ub}@{uu}

   You can use this variable to define the foldername where all  replyed
messages come in.

@{b}Example:@{ub}

     @{b}@{fg highlight}UMS v10@{fg text}@{ub}

     ReplyWizard.ReplyFolder = "MailReplys"

     @{b}@{fg highlight}UMS v11@{fg text}@{ub}

     ( ReplyWizard.ReplyFolder "MailReplys" )

@{b}Default:@{ub}

     "mailreplys"

@{b}Remark:@{ub}

     This variable is optional.

@endnode

@node ArchivBit "ReplyWizard.ArchivBit"
@toc Config
@next Folders
@prev ReplyFolder


@{b}@{u}ReplyWizard.ArchivBit@{ub}@{uu}

   You can use this variable to define if the archivbit should be set or
not.

@{b}Example:@{ub}

     @{b}@{fg highlight}UMS v10@{fg text}@{ub}

     ReplyWizard.ArchivBit = "Yes"

     @{b}@{fg highlight}UMS v11@{fg text}@{ub}

     ( ReplyWizard.ArchivBit "Yes" )

@{b}Default:@{ub}

     "No"

@{b}Remark:@{ub}

     This variable is optional.

@endnode

@node Folders "ReplyWizard.Folders"
@toc Config
@next ForceFolders
@prev ArchivBit


@{b}@{u}ReplyWizard.Folders@{ub}@{uu}

   You can use this variable to define the folders  which  were  scanned
for  new,  nonreplyed  messages with the attribute receipt-request resp.
audit-request.

@{b}Example:@{ub}

     @{b}@{fg highlight}UMS v10@{fg text}@{ub}

     ReplyWizard.Folders = "InterNET
     FidoNET
     AmigaNET"

     @{b}@{fg highlight}UMS v11@{fg text}@{ub}

     ( ReplyWizard.Folders "InterNET\\nFidoNET\\nAmigaNET\\n" )

@{b}Default:@{ub}

     none

@{b}Remark:@{ub}

     This variable is optional.

@endnode

@node ForceFolders "ReplyWizard.ForceFolders"
@toc Config
@next WizardName
@prev Folders


@{b}@{u}ReplyWizard.ForceFolders@{ub}@{uu}

   You can use this variable to define the folders  which  were  scanned
for  new,  nonreplyed  messages with unset attribute receipt. @{b}Attention:@{ub}
The use of this variable were recommended only well  versed  UMS  users,
because you can easy create endless replyes if the attribute receipt was
lost.

@{b}Example:@{ub}

     @{b}@{fg highlight}UMS v10@{fg text}@{ub}

     ReplyWizard.ForceFolders = "BugReports
     Important"

     @{b}@{fg highlight}UMS v11@{fg text}@{ub}

     ( ReplyWizard.ForceFolders "BugReports\\nImportant\\n" )

@{b}Default:@{ub}

     none

@{b}Remark:@{ub}

     This variable is optional.

@endnode

@node WizardName "ReplyWizard.WizardName"
@toc Config
@next Name
@prev ForceFolders


@{b}@{u}ReplyWizard.WizardName@{ub}@{uu}

   You can use this variable to define a imaginationname of the  sender.
(For this user a entry in the UMS.config is required !) If this variable
wasn't defined the realname will be used.

@{b}Example:@{ub}

     @{b}@{fg highlight}UMS v10@{fg text}@{ub}

     ReplyWizard.WizardName = "ReplyWizard"

     @{b}@{fg highlight}UMS v11@{fg text}@{ub}

     ( ReplyWizard.WizardName "ReplyWizard" )

@{b}Default:@{ub}

     none (the realname is used)

@{b}Remark:@{ub}

     This variable is optional.

@endnode

@node Name "ReplyWizard.Name"
@toc Config
@next Address
@prev WizardName


@{b}@{u}ReplyWizard.Name@{ub}@{uu} resp. @{b}@{u}ReplyWizard.Name.<Folder>@{ub}@{uu}

   You can  use  this  variable  to  define  the  replyname.  (see  also
IntuiNewsGuide 'The Mail Window/String Gadgets/Reply-To').

@{b}Examples:@{ub}

     @{b}@{fg highlight}UMS v10@{fg text}@{ub}

     ReplyWizard.Name = "Andreas Baum"

     ReplyWizard.Name.FidoNET = "Andreas Baum"

     @{b}@{fg highlight}UMS v11@{fg text}@{ub}

     ( ReplyWizard.Name "Andreas Baum" )

     ( ReplyWizard.Name.FidoNET "Andreas Baum" )

@{b}Default:@{ub}

     none

@{b}Remark:@{ub}

     This variable is optional.

@endnode

@node Address "ReplyWizard.Address"
@toc Config
@next Subject
@prev Name


@{b}@{u}ReplyWizard.Address@{ub}@{uu} resp. @{b}@{u}ReplyWizard.Address.<Folder>@{ub}@{uu}

   You can use this variable  to  define  the  replyaddress.  (see  also
IntuiNewsGuide 'The Mail Window/String Gadgets/Reply-To').

@{b}Examples:@{ub}

     @{b}@{fg highlight}UMS v10@{fg text}@{ub}

     ReplyWizard.Address = "2:2490/1370.6@FidoNET"

     ReplyWizard.Address.InterNET = "fatso@turtle.insider.sub.de"

     @{b}@{fg highlight}UMS v11@{fg text}@{ub}

     ( ReplyWizard.Address "2:2490/1370.6@FidoNET" )

     ( ReplyWizard.Address.InterNET "fatso@turtle.insider.sub.de" )

@{b}Default:@{ub}

     none

@{b}Reamrk:@{ub}

     This variable is optional.

@endnode

@node Subject "ReplyWizard.Subject"
@toc Config
@next Msg
@prev Address


@{b}@{u}ReplyWizard.Subject@{ub}@{uu} resp. @{b}@{u}ReplyWizard.Subject.<Folder>@{ub}@{uu}

   You can use this variable to define the subject for  the  reply.  The
following known variables were supported:

     "%%" for the per cent sign.
     "%d" for the creation date and time of the original message.
     "%n" for the name of the original sender.
     "%s" for the subject of the original sender.

@{b}Examples:@{ub}

     @{b}@{fg highlight}UMS v10@{fg text}@{ub}

     ReplyWizard.Subject = "Reply your Mail: %s"

     ReplyWizard.Subject.FidoNET = "Reply your FidoMail: %s"

     @{b}@{fg highlight}UMS v11@{fg text}@{ub}

     ( ReplyWizard.Subject "Reply your Mail: %s" )

     ( ReplyWizard.Subject.FidoNET "Reply your FidoMail: %s" )

@{b}Default:@{ub}

     none

@{b}Remark:@{ub}

     This variable is required.

@endnode

@node Msg "ReplyWizard.Msg"
@toc Config
@next Config
@prev Subject


@{b}@{u}ReplyWizard.Msg@{ub}@{uu} resp. @{b}@{u}ReplyWizard.Msg.<Folder>@{ub}@{uu}

   You can use this variable to define the text or the filename (use a @{b}$@{ub}
in  front  of the filename) for the reply. The following known variables
were supported:

     "%%" for the per cent sign.
     "%d" for the creation date and time of the original message.
     "%n" for the name of the original sender.
     "%s" for the subject of the original sender.

@{b}Examples:@{ub}

     @{b}@{fg highlight}UMS v10@{fg text}@{ub}

     ReplyWizard.Msg = "Hello %n,*n
     I received your Mail about %s at %d.
     I will answer you in a few days.*n
     Bye, Andreas"

     ReplyWizard.Msg.InterNET = "Hi %n,*n
     I received your InterNET-Mail about
     %s
     at %d.*n
     bye, Andreas (fatso@turtle.insider.sub.de)"

     ReplyWizard.Msg.AmigaNET = "$UMS:Texts/PGPFingerPrint"

     @{b}@{fg highlight}UMS v11@{fg text}@{ub}

     ( ReplyWizard.Msg
         "Hello %n,\\n"
         "\\n"
         "I received your Mail about %s at %d.\\n"
         "I will answer you in a few days.\\n"
         "\\n"
         "Bye, Andreas\\n"
     )

     ( ReplyWizard.Msg.InterNET =
         "Hi %n,\\n"
         "\\n"
         "I received your InterNET-Mail about\\n"
         "%s\\n"
         "at %d.\\n"
         "\\n"
         "bye, Andreas (fatso@turtle.insider.sub.de)\\n"
     )

     ( ReplyWizard.Msg.AmigaNET "$UMS:Texts/PGPFingerPrint" )

@{b}Default:@{ub}

     none

@{b}Remark:@{ub}

     This variable is required.

@endnode

@node Start "Starting ReplyWizard"
@next Output
@prev Config


@{b}@{u}Starting from a shell@{ub}@{uu}

   If you start ReplyWizard from a shell you may  supply  the  following
arguments:

@{b}NAME/A@{ub}
     The name of the UMS user.

@{b}PASSWORD/A@{ub}
     The password for this user. The password is case sensitive.

@{b}SERVER/K@{ub}
     The UMS server to use. You must use the keyword @{b}SERVER@{ub} in front  of
     this argument.

@{b}Example:@{ub}

     1> ReplyWizard "Andreas Baum" Secret

@endnode

@node Output "Output"
@next PGP
@prev Start


@{b}@{u}Output of ReplyWizard@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}.@{ub} = New mail but no RECEIPT-REQUEST or AUDIT-REQUEST found.
@{b}+@{ub} = Create receiptmail with from- replyname and from- replyaddress.
@{b}>@{ub} = Found a new mail with a 'attributereceipt'.
@{b}*@{ub} = Create receiptmail with 'attributename and -address'.
@{b}!@{ub} = New mail but already replyed.

@endnode

